Thomas has options. Here's why he picks the Execution Engine:

**Vs. executive coach (€150-300/hour):** A coach meets you once a week. Between sessions, nothing measures your execution. The EE confronts you every single day with a number. A coach is opinion-based. The EE is data-based. A coach costs €7,000-15,000/year. The EE costs €997 once.

**Vs. productivity apps (Notion, Todoist, Sunsama):** Apps track tasks. They don't measure execution rate. They don't confront you when you drift. They don't pattern-match across weeks to show you why you keep failing on Wednesdays. And when you stop using the app after 2 weeks (like Thomas always does), nobody notices.

**Vs. accountability platforms (Coach.me, Focusmate):** Generic check-ins with strangers. No personalization. No vault extraction. No cross-engine intelligence. No execution score.

**The "only we" statement:** The Execution Engine is the only system that gives you an objective, daily execution score — a number, not a feeling — powered by an AI that knows your goals, reads your patterns, and confronts you when your behavior contradicts your stated priorities. It runs on your own infrastructure, it's built for you specifically, and it remembers everything.

**The real differentiator is the execution score.** Not self-hosted. Not AI. The number. Nobody else gives Thomas a weekly percentage that says "you executed 34% of your strategic priorities this week." That number is the product.

