## 5. THE ENGINE ECOSYSTEM

Four engines. Execution Engine is the core. The others are add-ons or internal tools.

### 5.1 Execution Engine (THE CORE — for clients)

**Problem:** "I know what to do. I just don't do it consistently."
**Solution:** Done-for-you AI accountability system. Measures what you do vs. what you said. Every day. Every week. For 12 weeks.

Core features:
- Keystone extraction (AI reads your notes → personal operating system)
- 12-week goal tracking with milestones
- Daily morning priorities (AI-generated, aligned to goals)
- Daily accountability check-in (facts, not feelings)
- Weekly review with execution score (% lead actions completed)
- Contradiction detector (behavior vs. stated values)

What makes it different:
- It confronts. No "great job!" when you didn't do the work.
- It measures. Execution score is a number, not a feeling.
- It's yours. Runs on your dedicated server. You own your data.
- It's done for you. You don't build anything. We set it up.

### 5.2 Intelligence Engine (ADD-ON — for clients + own use)

**Problem:** "I spend hours reading news and still miss what matters."
**Solution:** Personalized signal-vs-noise filter. Scans 500+ sources, AI-scores relevance, delivers only what survived a 30-day hype filter.

Core features:
- RSS/API collectors (Reddit, YouTube, HN, GitHub, HuggingFace, Tweakers)
- AI scoring per content pillar (via Ollama, €0 cost)
- Hype filter: 2 revalidation cycles (day 15 + day 30)
- Breaking bypass for score ≥9
- Weekly intelligence briefing
- Hype-ratio stats ("74% of trending news was noise")

### 5.3 Personal Engine (ADD-ON — for clients)

**Problem:** "My ideas, notes, and tasks are scattered across 12 tools."
**Solution:** AI second brain via Telegram/Slack. Remembers everything, manages calendar, retrieves anything in seconds.

Core features:
- Memory store with semantic search
- Calendar + email integration (Google Calendar, Gmail)
- Cross-engine morning briefing (combines all engines)
- On-demand knowledge retrieval

### 5.4 Publish Engine (INTERNAL TOOLING — for own GTM, not a client product)

**Problem:** "I have IE signals and content ideas but publishing is manual and fragmented."
**Solution:** Self-hosted multi-platform publishing pipeline. Takes IE output + own content, generates drafts via Claude, publishes after human review.

**Why it's not scope creep:** Without consistent content, there are no pilots. This turns "2 hours writing LinkedIn posts" into "10 minutes approving AI drafts." It's a GTM accelerator.

Core features:
- Content queue with status tracking: draft → pending_review → approved → scheduled → published
- Claude API draft generation per platform (tone, length, format adapted per channel)
- Human review via Telegram notification with approve/reject
- Scheduled publishing via n8n crons + Postiz (or direct API calls)
- Engagement tracking (build when you have 4+ weeks of posting data)

**Phased platform rollout:**

| Phase | Platforms | When |
|-------|----------|------|
| First | LinkedIn + X | Phase 2 (parallel with EE dogfooding) |
| Second | YouTube Shorts + Instagram | After pilots, when video content makes sense |
| Third | TikTok | When broader reach beyond Thomas is needed |

**All five platforms supported. Build LinkedIn + X first. The rest when needed.**

**Platform API summary:**

| Platform | Post via API | Cost | Auth/Review | n8n support |
|----------|-------------|------|-------------|-------------|
| LinkedIn | Yes | Free | "Share on LinkedIn" (auto-approved, 60-day tokens) or Community Management API (business entity, refresh tokens) | Native node |
| X/Twitter | Yes | Free tier ~500 posts/mo. Pay-per-use ~$0.01/post | Developer account | Native node + HTTP |
| YouTube | Yes (incl. Shorts) | Free (quota-based, ~100 uploads/day) | OAuth verification 2-4 weeks | HTTP Request node |
| Instagram | Yes (Business/Creator only) | Free | Meta app review 2-4 weeks, Facebook Page required | Community nodes + HTTP |
| TikTok | Yes (Direct Post + Draft) | Free | Compliance audit for public visibility | HTTP Request node |

**Publishing middleware:** Postiz (open-source, AGPL-3.0, 30+ platforms, Docker). Pin to v2.11.3. Alternative: skip Postiz, use direct API calls via n8n HTTP nodes — less elegant but zero extra infra.

**Content pipeline:**

```
IE signal (scored ≥7) OR own content idea
    → n8n: Claude API generates platform-specific drafts
    → Supabase: content_items (status: draft)
    → n8n: Telegram notification with approve/reject webhooks
    → Human approves → status: approved
    → n8n cron: publishes at optimal time via Postiz or direct API
```

