### 10.5 Agent architecture

No workflow spaghetti. One Claude agent with tools. n8n only for webhooks and crons.

```
Message in (Telegram/Slack)
    → n8n webhook (3 nodes)
    → Claude API with tools
    → Claude decides what to do
    → Tool calls: save_memory, manage_goal, search_knowledge, etc.
    → n8n executes tools (Supabase queries)
    → Claude generates response
    → n8n sends response back
```

New features = edit system prompt + optionally add a tool. No new workflows.

Cron workflows (minimal):
1. Morning briefing (07:00) — 3 nodes
2. Accountability check-in (17:00) — 3 nodes
3. Weekly review (Sunday 18:00) — 3 nodes
4. IE scan (Sunday 06:00 + Wednesday 06:00) — uses Ollama
5. Publish Engine: scheduled posting (cron per platform) — 5 nodes

